24:11.220 --> 24:20.160
This is Bill Vernon and David Crews. 1980 was a successful year for science
fiction author George Martin. Martin received the Hugo Award for his short

24:20.160 --> 24:28.820
story, The Way of Crossing Dragon, and both the Hugo and Nebula Awards for his
novelette, Sand Kings. Sand Kings is one of those timeless stories that is

24:28.820 --> 24:38.220
destined to be a classic. In 1981, the novel Windhaven was published. It was
written by Martin in conjunction with Lisa Tuttle. Well, every collaboration is

24:38.220 --> 24:49.720
different. It's like a marriage. There are no rules. What we said was a very
easy sort of collaboration. We would talk about collaboration with good friends

24:49.720 --> 24:57.680
and all that. When we got together, we talked about the initial story. Then
we're going to write it. The way it would work is one of us would start. We'd

24:57.680 --> 25:06.680
write a certain amount of pages, a certain 20 pages, shift them up to the other.
The second one would rewrite that section. I'm going to go on and write some

25:06.680 --> 25:15.800
more material. And that. First, rather, we'd rewrite the portion. The second one
would go on. For each of us, essentially, we'd write the other one's section.

25:16.120 --> 25:26.460
And we alternated it in the first draft. After having worked out the broad
outlines of the plot together in the country. And it all took place too, now. We

25:26.460 --> 25:34.580
learned that Windhaven as a novel was not the original intent of Martin and
Tuttle. Rather, it started out as a shorter story. Actually, it began as a much

25:34.580 --> 25:42.680
shorter story. A thing called My Brother's Wings that we completed in
collaboration. It showed it to Ben Bova. It doesn't really run satisfactorily.

25:43.120 --> 25:50.220
It seems to be much longer. And he was right. And we went back and expanded it.
And we produced the storms at Windhaven. But I think by the time we finished

25:50.220 --> 26:03.040
that, it was pretty clear to us that. There needed to be more. By the time we
did One Wing, years later, we let years relax in between the writing of the

26:03.040 --> 26:11.180
first and second parts. We knew exactly what we were doing. We had the structure
of the entire book and the role that One Wing played, both in relation to storms

26:11.180 --> 26:21.000
that came before and in relation to the fall that came after. So by then, One
Wing was written, both as an individual and today and as part of the book. Much

26:21.000 --> 26:28.980
of the novel's action is centered on the characters flying about on wings
mounted on and powered by their arms. We asked Martin about the research you did

26:28.980 --> 26:39.640
to ensure that the mechanical aspects of flying are practical. Well, I did some
research on hang gliding. I got, you know, I got some books on it and, and read

26:39.640 --> 26:48.840
so I'd be able to give the story to various military required. And we must have
done fairly well in terms of accuracy. We had hang gliding magazines serialized

26:48.840 --> 26:55.660
storms of wind tape and effort came out. So, obviously, they would not have done
it if they'd been too full of egregious errors.

26:58.460 --> 27:06.540
And in fact, I noticed, I picked up, years after, like, the original story came
out in hang gliding magazine, I picked up another issue of hang gliding

27:06.540 --> 27:17.880
magazine. I discovered that all these people were selling Windhaven altimeters
and, you know, the Windhaven brand, uh, Regalo sales, and, uh, you know, like a

27:17.880 --> 27:28.240
brand name or something like that. So, impressed someone out there. Martin
explained the plans he and Tuttle have for Windhaven. My conception of it is as

27:28.240 --> 27:40.340
a, as a real trilogy. That is to say, neither one big book nor a series of
unrelated books. But, essentially, we began two stories in the beginning. We

27:40.340 --> 27:50.080
began the story of Maris and Lesser Amberly, which ended at the end of
Windhaven. And we also began a story about the social changes initiated by

27:50.080 --> 28:03.040
Maris. And that, that social changes ripping through the culture, helping all
sorts of things. That story is not concluded. That story requires more violence.

28:04.220 --> 28:16.480
But, hopefully, there's only, there will only be the two of them that we have
originally conceived. If, uh, you know, if that is, if you look around ten years

28:16.480 --> 28:25.640
from now and you find that I'm working on the ninth Windhaven book, at least so
you will know that I have sold out. And, hopefully, that, that, that will not

28:25.640 --> 28:25.960
happen.

